'''Taur-nu-Fuin''' means "Forest of Darkness" in [[Sindarin]] (''[[taur]]'', "forest"; ''[[nu]]'', "under"; ''[[fuin]]'', "night, darkness"); in the ''[[Lay of Leithian]]'', it is translated as "Forest of Nightshade". It can refer to:
* '''[[Taur-nu-Fuin (Dorthonion)|Taur-nu-Fuin]], the Forest of [[Dorthonion]] in [[Beleriand]] which existed in the [[First Age]].'''
* [[Mirkwood|Taur-nu-Fuin]], the name for the Forest of [[Mirkwood]] in [[Rhovanion]] in the [[Third Age]], before it was renamed ''[[Eryn Lasgalen]]''.
